---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About — plangs!" description="About the plangs! programming languages database.">
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-prose">
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-3xl">About plangs!</h1>
    <p class="mb-3">
      plangs! is an open database of programming languages and how they relate — the paradigms they embrace, their type systems, the
      platforms they target, their licenses, and who influenced whom.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-3">
      The data lives as one YAML file per node in the open-source repository. Every language page has a machine-readable
      <a href="/nim.md" class="underline">markdown twin</a> and the whole site is described for agents at
      <a href="/llms.txt" class="underline">/llms.txt</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
